OL,3,CRenovate houses rather than build new
OL,4,Cones, argues Tameside landlord
OL,6,FHe said: "Once the property has been
OL,7,Fempty for more than two years they
OL,8,Fwould serve the owner with this, which
OL,9,Fwould give them the opportunity to put
OL,10,Fit into a habitable state. They could
OL,11,Fthen put it out to rent, or sell it,
OL,12,For live there themselves."
OL,14,FIf the owner of the home does not make
OL,15,Fthe necessary renovations, the local
OL,16,Fauthority would be able to do it
OL,17,Fthemselves.
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G3/10
