OL,3,CRenovate houses rather than build new
OL,4,Cones, argues Tameside landlord
OL,6,FStephen said: "The local authority can
OL,7,Fseize the property and have the works
OL,8,Fcarried out. Then they rent it out on
OL,9,Fthe social side and that rent would
OL,10,Frepay the local authority for the cost
OL,11,Fof the works they've done.
OL,13,F"The person who owns the property
OL,14,Fhasn't lost it, and once everything's
OL,15,Fbeen repaid to the local property they
OL,16,Fcould carry on receiving the rent
OL,17,Fknowing it's providing a home to a
OL,18,Ffamily that needs it."
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G4/10
