OL,3,CRenovate houses rather than build new
OL,4,Cones, argues Tameside landlord
OL,6,F"So I think the fact that there's
OL,7,Fgoing to be more housing is really
OL,8,Fgood."
OL,10,FStephen argues that his plan would
OL,11,Fhelp people like Claire, but with
OL,12,Fcouncils struggling to provide basic
OL,13,Fservices many will argue renovating
OL,14,Fhouses is a luxury they cannot afford.
OL,16,FInstead many councils, including
OL,17,FTameside, charge an increased rate of
OL,18,Fcouncil tax to owners of empty houses,
OL,19,Fwith the amount increasing to up to
OL,20,F400% depending on the length of
OL,21,Fvacancy.
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G8/10
